Con la condición de 
\noun on 
Brewster
\noun default 
, la ley de 
\noun on 
Snell
\noun default 
, etc, escribimos:
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
\tan\theta_{1} & = & n_{v}\\
\sin\theta_{1} & = & n_{v}\sin\theta_{1}'\\
n_{v}\cos\theta_{1} & = & \cos\theta_{1}'\\
\sin\theta_{1}' & = & \cos\theta_{1}\\
\theta_{1}'+\theta_{1} & = & \frac{\pi}{2}\\
\tan\theta' & = & n_{v}\\
\tan\theta_{2} & = & \frac{1}{n_{v}}\\
\sin\theta_{2} & = & n_{v}\sin\theta_{2}'\\
n_{v}\cos\theta_{2} & = & \cos\theta_{2}'\\
\sin\theta_{2}' & = & \cos\theta_{2}\\
\theta_{2}'+\theta_{2} & = & \frac{\pi}{2}\end{eqnarray*}

